Bashar al-Assad, the Syrian president, accepts the resignation of the country's government, following two weeks of anti-government protests that have gripped Syria. However Muhammad Naji al-Otari, the resigning prime minister will continue to serve as caretaker Prime Minister. (Al Jazeera) (Syrian Arab News Agency) (SBS World News)The Libyan oil minister, Shukri Ghanem, reportedly defects to Tunisia. (Al Jazeera)Gunmen open fire on protesters in the city of Ta'izz with 35 people being injured. (Reuters)